            "Many well-known birds, such as hawks, eagles, kites, harriers and Old World vultures are included in this group.",
            "Doves & Pigeons",
            "The falcons and caracaras are around 60 species of diurnal birds of prey that make up the order Falconidae. The family is divided into two subfamilies, Polyborinae, which includes the caracaras and forest falcons, and Falconinae, the falcons, kestrels and falconets (Microhierax and Spiziapteryx). ",
